<item>
            <title>[CODEC-254] ColognePhonetic does not treat the letter H correctly</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CODEC-254</link>
                <project id="12310464" key="CODEC">Commons Codec</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;With the fix in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CODEC-250&quot; title=&quot;Wrong value calculated by Cologne Phonetic if a special character is placed between equal letters&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CODEC-250&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CODEC-250&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; the letter H is not treaten correct any more.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A String &apos;shch&apos; is coded as 8 and not as 84. (This string is sometimes in foreign surnames)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The reasen is the letter h is ignored completely and not stored in the lastChar anymore.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
