                            <comment id="16793822" author="garydgregory" created="Fri, 15 Mar 2019 17:53:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We welcome patches on github, with unit tests.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16865466" author="sebb@apache.org" created="Mon, 17 Jun 2019 09:21:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I agree, the code currently handles SHCH incorrectly.&lt;br/&gt;
I&apos;ve checked with the Perl Text::Phonetic::Koeln module and that says SHCH =&amp;gt; 84.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think the error occurs because the code only takes account of H as the next character, and ignores the fact that it affects the previous character. So it looks like the C directly follows the S.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16865776" author="sebb@apache.org" created="Mon, 17 Jun 2019 17:02:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;4f8662a  &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CODEC-254&quot; title=&quot;ColognePhonetic does not treat the letter H correctly&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CODEC-254&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CODEC-254&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; - ColognePhonetic does not treat the letter H correct&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16866636" author="melloware" created="Tue, 18 Jun 2019 14:12:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=sebb&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;sebb&quot;&gt;sebb&lt;/a&gt; This looks awfully similar to this issue?  &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CODEC-255&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CODEC-255&lt;/a&gt;  Is it possible it is fixed also?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
